  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 12\"><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></math>. It&rsquo;s given that function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi></math> is a quadratic function where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis negative 20 right parenthesis equals 0\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis negative 4 right parenthesis equals 0\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. It follows that the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane passes through&nbsp;the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis negative 20 comma 0 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis negative 4 comma 0 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. When the graph of a quadratic function contains two points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis a comma 0 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis b comma 0 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, the <em>x</em>-coordinate of the vertex of the graph is the average of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\"><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math>.&nbsp;Therefore, the <em>x</em>-coordinate of the vertex of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction negative 20 plus left parenthesis negative 4 right parenthesis Over 2 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 12\"><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></math>. It's given that the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane has a vertex at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis r comma negative 64 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. It follows that the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 12\"><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></math>.</p>",
